Class UnmodifiableDishonestMap<K,V>

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>

    public class UnmodifiableDishonestMap<K,V>
extends DishonestMap<K,V>
    An unmodifiable variant of DishonestMap.

    Attempts to add or remove key mappings throw UnsupportedOperationException.
    Note that the backing map MAY change; if so, changes are reflected in this UnmodifiableDishonestMap.
    Author:
    A248

    • Constructor Detail

      • UnmodifiableDishonestMap

        public UnmodifiableDishonestMap(Map<K,V> original,
                                UnaryOperator<V> processor)
        Creates an UnmodifiableDishonestMap using the given map as the backing map and the UnaryOperator to process Map.get(Object) operations.

        See DishonestMap.DishonestMap(Map, UnaryOperator) for more information.

        Example: creating an unmodifiable map of unmodifiable submaps. Map<String, Map> totallyUnmodifiableMegaMap = new UnmodifiableDishonestMap<String, Map>(existingMap, Collections::unmodifiableMap); where existingMap is the original map.
        Parameters:
        original - the original, backing map
        processor - with which to modify #get results
